<feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><title>Notes</title><link href="http://znotdead.github.io/" rel="alternate"></link><link href="http://znotdead.github.io/feeds/vim.atom.xml" rel="self"></link><id>http://znotdead.github.io/</id><updated>2015-01-15T00:00:00+01:00</updated><entry><title>NORMAL MODE: Increment/Decrement numbers</title><link href="http://znotdead.github.io/increment_decrement_numbers_in_normal_mode.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2015-01-15T00:00:00+01:00</updated><author><name>znotdead</name></author><id>tag:znotdead.github.io,2012-12-10:increment_decrement_numbers_in_normal_mode.html</id><summary type="html">&lt;h3&gt;NORMAL MODE: Increment/Decrement numbers&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;How do you change 23 to 33?&lt;br /&gt;
Probably you press "r" with cursor under 2 and then "3". But!&lt;br /&gt;
How you change 99 to 100? In this case you need to go to Insert mode or some other variants. But it the simples way on my opinion:&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;code&gt;CTRL-a&lt;/code&gt; Increment number right of the cursor&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;code&gt;CTRL-x&lt;/code&gt; Decrement number right of the cursor&lt;/p&gt;</summary><category term="Vim"></category><category term="normal mode"></category></entry><entry><title>NERDTree: refresh tree</title><link href="http://znotdead.github.io/nerdtree_refresh_tree.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2015-01-15T00:00:00+01:00</updated><author><name>znotdead</name></author><id>tag:znotdead.github.io,2012-12-10:nerdtree_refresh_tree.html</id><summary type="html">&lt;h3&gt;NERDTree: refresh tree&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;r&lt;/code&gt;  - Recursively refresh the current directory&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;code&gt;R&lt;/code&gt;  - Recursively refresh the current root&lt;/p&gt;</summary><category term="Vim"></category><category term="NERDTree"></category></entry><entry><title>NORMAL_MODE: Insert empty lines</title><link href="http://znotdead.github.io/insert_empty_lines_in_normal_mode.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2015-01-15T00:00:00+01:00</updated><author><name>znotdead</name></author><id>tag:znotdead.github.io,2012-12-10:insert_empty_lines_in_normal_mode.html</id><summary type="html">&lt;h3&gt;NORMAL MODE: Insert empty lines&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I can't found any mapping for that and there are many recipes. pressing o or O ans then &lt;Esc&gt; not very convenient.&lt;br /&gt;
The easiest for me is:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;normal &lt;span class="k"&gt;o&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;and&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;normal O
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;you can map this command on anything you like&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or you can map :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class="nb"&gt;nnoremap&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;Enter&lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;o&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;ESC&lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</summary><category term="Vim"></category><category term="normal mode"></category></entry><entry><title>run file in console wile editing</title><link href="http://znotdead.github.io/run_file_in_console_wile_editing.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2015-01-15T00:00:00+01:00</updated><author><name>znotdead</name></author><id>tag:znotdead.github.io,2012-12-10:run_file_in_console_wile_editing.html</id><summary type="html">&lt;h3&gt;run file in console wile editing&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;:!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;command&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;%&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;For example to check your code during editing:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;:!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;pep8&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;%&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="o"&gt;:!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;pyflakes&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;%&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="o"&gt;:!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;pylint&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="o"&gt;%&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</summary><category term="Vim"></category></entry><entry><title>NORMAL MODE: transpose two letters</title><link href="http://znotdead.github.io/transpose_two_letters.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2015-01-15T00:00:00+01:00</updated><author><name>znotdead</name></author><id>tag:znotdead.github.io,2012-12-10:transpose_two_letters.html</id><summary type="html">&lt;h3&gt;NORMAL MODE: transpose two letters&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;xp&lt;/code&gt; - transpose two letters (delete and paste). very simple =)&lt;/p&gt;</summary><category term="Vim"></category><category term="normal mode"></category></entry><entry><title>VISUAL MODE: editing</title><link href="http://znotdead.github.io/visual_mode_editing.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2015-01-15T00:00:00+01:00</updated><author><name>znotdead</name></author><id>tag:znotdead.github.io,2012-12-10:visual_mode_editing.html</id><summary type="html">&lt;h3&gt;VISUAL MODE: editing&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;CTRL-v&lt;/code&gt; Visual select block mode&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Commands:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
once you have rectangular block, you can remove block with &lt;code&gt;d&lt;/code&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
insert text in front of the block with capital &lt;code&gt;I&lt;/code&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
append text after the block with capital &lt;code&gt;A&lt;/code&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
change text with &lt;code&gt;c&lt;/code&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
cut text using &lt;code&gt;x&lt;/code&gt; and paste using &lt;code&gt;p&lt;/code&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
change text to single characters using &lt;code&gt;R&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</summary><category term="Vim"></category><category term="visual mode"></category></entry><entry><title>VISUAL MODE: Search and replace in selected</title><link href="http://znotdead.github.io/visual_mode_search_and_replace_in_selected.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2015-01-15T00:00:00+01:00</updated><author><name>znotdead</name></author><id>tag:znotdead.github.io,2012-12-10:visual_mode_search_and_replace_in_selected.html</id><summary type="html">&lt;h3&gt;VISUAL MODE: Search and replace in selected&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;on select there are&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;start&lt;/span&gt; line
`&lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;start&lt;/span&gt; character
&amp;#39;&lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt; line
`&lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt; character
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Imagine that you have visual region selected. so to replace press &lt;code&gt;:&lt;/code&gt; and in command there is &lt;code&gt;:'&amp;lt;,'&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; in command line already entered. So you should add to this &lt;code&gt;s/&amp;lt;word1&amp;gt;/&amp;lt;word2&amp;gt;/g&lt;/code&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
or if You want to change in last selected region in Normal mode type:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="s1"&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;lt;,&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;  &lt;span class="k"&gt;s&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="sr"&gt;/start/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;end&lt;/span&gt;/&lt;span class="k"&gt;g&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;to search by only visual region you should in Normal mode:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="err"&gt;\&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;%&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="n"&gt;Vword1&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</summary><category term="Vim"></category><category term="visual mode"></category></entry><entry><title>Delete lines containing pattern</title><link href="http://znotdead.github.io/delete_lines_containing_pattern.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2015-01-15T00:00:00+01:00</updated><author><name>znotdead</name></author><id>tag:znotdead.github.io,2012-12-10:delete_lines_containing_pattern.html</id><summary type="html">&lt;h3&gt;Delete lines containing pattern&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For example, I need to delete all lines containing "WORD"&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To view all lines to be removed:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;g&lt;/span&gt;/WORD
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;To remove lines:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;g&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="sr"&gt;/WORD/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;d&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Or negative:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;g&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="sr"&gt;/profile/&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="k"&gt;d&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</summary><category term="Vim"></category></entry><entry><title>NERDTree: show hidden files</title><link href="http://znotdead.github.io/nerdtree_show_hidden_files.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2015-01-15T00:00:00+01:00</updated><author><name>znotdead</name></author><id>tag:znotdead.github.io,2012-12-10:nerdtree_show_hidden_files.html</id><summary type="html">&lt;h3&gt;NERDTree: show hidden files&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;from man:&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;code&gt;*'NERDTreeShowHidden'*&lt;/code&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Values: 0 or 1. Default: 0.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This option tells vim whether to display hidden files by default.&lt;br /&gt;
This option can be dynamically toggled, per tree, with the &lt;code&gt;|NERDTree-I|&lt;/code&gt; mapping.&lt;br /&gt;
Use one of the follow lines to set this option:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; NERDTreeShowHidden&lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="m"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class="p"&gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="k"&gt;let&lt;/span&gt; NERDTreeShowHidden&lt;span class="p"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="m"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</summary><category term="Vim"></category><category term="NERDTree"></category></entry><entry><title>Recording and repeat actions</title><link href="http://znotdead.github.io/recording_and_repeat_actions.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2015-01-15T00:00:00+01:00</updated><author><name>znotdead</name></author><id>tag:znotdead.github.io,2012-12-10:recording_and_repeat_actions.html</id><summary type="html">&lt;h3&gt;Recording and repeat actions&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Turn on recording: &lt;code&gt;q&amp;lt;letter&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
Turn Off recording: &lt;code&gt;q&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It records everything you type.&lt;br /&gt;
To reply it:  &lt;code&gt;@&amp;lt;letter&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Record move, insert, search...&lt;/p&gt;</summary><category term="Vim"></category></entry><entry><title>VIM: diff usage</title><link href="http://znotdead.github.io/vim_diff_usage.html" rel="alternate"></link><updated>2015-01-15T00:00:00+01:00</updated><author><name>znotdead</name></author><id>tag:znotdead.github.io,2012-12-09:vim_diff_usage.html</id><summary type="html">&lt;h3&gt;VIM: diff usage&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Small cheat sheet for using vimdiff&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;code&gt;vimdiff&lt;/code&gt; - edit two or three versions of a file with Vim and show differences&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Commands:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;code&gt;do&lt;/code&gt; – Get changes from other window into the current window.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;code&gt;dp&lt;/code&gt; – Put the changes from current window into the other window.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;code&gt;]c&lt;/code&gt; – Jump to the next change.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;code&gt;[c&lt;/code&gt; – Jump to the previous change.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;code&gt;Ctrl W + Ctrl W&lt;/code&gt; – Switch to the other split window.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;code&gt;:diffupdate&lt;/code&gt; – diff update&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;code&gt;:syntax off&lt;/code&gt; – syntax off&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;code&gt;zo&lt;/code&gt; – open folded text&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;code&gt;zc&lt;/code&gt; – close folded text&lt;/p&gt;</summary><category term="Vim"></category></entry></feed>